{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2021-1124","published":"2021-04-07T11:02:46Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:17:13.978151Z","upstream":["CVE-2021-20229"],"summary":"postgresql security update","details":"PostgreSQL is an advanced Object-Relational database management system (DBMS) that supports almost all SQL constructs (including transactions, subselects and user-defined types and functions). The postgresql package includes the client programs and libraries that you&apos;ll need to access a PostgreSQL DBMS server.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nA flaw was found in PostgreSQL in versions before 13.2, before 12.6, before 11.11, before 10.16, before 9.6.21 and before 9.5.25. This flaw allows a user with SELECT privilege on one column to craft a special query that returns all columns of the table. The highest threat from this vulnerability is to confidentiality.(CVE-2021-20229)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"postgresql","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/postgresql&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"10.5-21.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["postgresql-test-10.5-20.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-debuginfo-10.5-20.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-help-10.5-20.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-10.5-20.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-debugsource-10.5-20.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-plperl-10.5-20.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-plpython3-10.5-20.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-libs-10.5-20.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-server-10.5-20.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-pltcl-10.5-20.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-contrib-10.5-20.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-test-rpm-macros-10.5-20.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-devel-10.5-20.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-static-10.5-20.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-test-rpm-macros-10.5-21.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-test-10.5-21.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-server-10.5-21.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-plperl-10.5-21.oe1.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-help-10.5-21.oe1.aarch64.rpm",